unresolved in all bands, implying a very compact size {\ensuremath{\lesssim}}200 pc in the UV. This suggests that the simultaneous buildup of compact stellar populations (i.e., galaxy bulges) and the central SMBH is ongoing even at z {\ensuremath{\gtrsim}} 7.}},
